<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. &#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Magazine Title</em>, Month day, year of publication, pages. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Smith, Alistair</span>. 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Chocolate Milk Key to Longevity</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Magazine Title">New Research International</span></em>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Month day, year of publication">December 15, 2056</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="pages">6&#45;7</span>.
</blockquote>
